Pre-requisite:

1. Install nodejs.
2. Install bower globaly

How to run:

1. Clone source from bitbucket.
2. Go to the root directory where the "package.json" file exists.
3. Open terminal and run: "sudo nmp install".
4. There will be some error related to phantomjs, ignore it 
   or run, "sudo nmp install" again.   
5. run, "bower install"   
6. System will ask you to select jquery version, select 4.
7. Rebuild node-sass: "sudo npm rebuild node-sass"
8. Use this command if you find some gulp related error:

	echo fs.inotify.max_user_watches=524288 | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf && sudo sysctl -p

9. run "gulp serve" to run the system
10.run "gulp build" to build the system 	


